title: Why Weather Prediction Is Still So Hard
description:
The U.S. experienced 18 separate billion-dollar weather or climate disasters in 2022, costing a total of $165 billion in damages. The disasters were also deadly, causing at least 474 direct or indirect fatalities, according to the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration.

In the U.S., NOAA is in charge of tracking weather and disseminating forecasts. It‚Äôs a complicated job that begins with collecting billions of observations per day on metrics like temperature, wind speed and moisture. This information is then fed into powerful supercomputers that produce weather models that meteorologists use to come up with forecasts. But these models are not perfect.

As climate change intensifies extreme weather events, accurate weather forecasting is becoming more important than ever. It‚Äôs why a new generation of private companies have cropped up to provide paying customers with hyperlocal, hyperspecific weather forecasting and data. The weather forecasting services industry in the U.S. was estimated to be worth about $17.4 billion in 2023, according to IBISWorld.

CNBC spoke with two such companies, Boston-based Tomorrow.io and Alameda, California-based Saildrone, to learn how their technology can help improve weather forecasting for NOAA and others.

title: Aliens vs Predator 2 - Alpha Character Bio - Baal
description:
Aliens vs Predator 2's (AvP2) developer, Monolith, wrote a detailed backstory for AvP2 and it's characters. However, most of this backstory was removed from the final version of the game.

Some of the backstory does remain in the final version of the game, but mainly as references to things that aren't expanded upon. Also some names of characters and places changed in the final version of the game.

Fortunately, I happened to stumble upon this previously unreleased backstory which was built for the alpha version of AvP2. In this audio narration of the backstory, I've added supporting video to go along with it.

The backstory is broken into the following:

1. Overview
2. Cast
3. Teams:
-The Marine Rescue Team
-The Corporate Team
-The Iron Bear Battalion
-The Alien Hive
-The Predator Sumar Clan
4. Some characters from each team.

This video highlights "Baal".

Enjoy!

[1] She holds a PhD degree in Islamic studies from the University of Glasgow, Scotland and was formerly a lecturer and assistant professor at the Faculty of Usul-al-Din at International Islamic University, Islamabad.[2][3] Hashmi founded Al-Huda International Welfare Foundation in 1994. The foundation started a number of schools to teach the Quran and Hadith to women in order to "help women become better observant muslims by helping them understand the Quran". The foundation now runs a network of schools, seminaries and social welfare projects.[4][5][6] In 2004, the foundation established the Al-Huda Institute in Mississauga (Toronto area), Ontario, Canada. This institute offers courses on exegesis of the Quran and Hadith and attracts students from a number of foreign countries such as Australia.[7][8]

She has gained popularity as a feminist scholar both in Pakistan and abroad, as evidenced by crowds of up to ten thousand that attend her religious lessons, called "Dars". Most followers come from liberal, literate and modern backgrounds; and most are women.[9][10] She has stated that her mission is to bring a renewal in Islam, through better understanding of the core scriptures. title: Nashville school shooting: City in shock after gunman kills 3 kids, 3 adults
description:
Nashville police released video Tuesday from a body-worn camera that shows a team of officers entering and searching an elementary school, then confronting and opening fire on an assailant who had murdered three children and three adults in the latest school shooting to roil the nation.

The dramatic, six-minute video supplements an earlier release, late Monday, of about two minutes of edited surveillance footage that shows the shooter's car driving up to the school, glass doors being shot out and the shooter ducking through one of them.

The new video from Officer Rex Engelbert's body cam shows a woman greeting police outside as they arrive at The Covenant School on Monday. "The kids are all locked down, but we have two kids that we don't know where they are," she tells police.

"OK, yes, ma'am," Engelbert replies.

The woman then directs officers to Fellowship Hall and says people inside had just heard gunshots. "Upstairs are a bunch of kids," she says.

This video does not show any physical violence.

title: The Mandalorian Episode 5 Breakdown HE'S BACK
description:
episode starts of with high magistrate carga on navarro 7 as the pirate ship looms over his town‚Äôs skies, as Gorian Shard hails him. Shard makes fun of Greef and says basically that he‚Äôs gone soft and rich, that he‚Äôs not the man he used to be. He blames Greef for killing his pirates in cold blood, doing the typical pirate thing where they manipulate and twist scenarios. Greef says it‚Äôs not a good idea to fire on Navarro 7 as he‚Äôs connected, and Shard laughs, telling him he‚Äôs not part of the new republic, nor is moff gideon protecting him anymore. Shard blows up the town of navarro and greef takes his townspeople to the outskirts of the city as he calls the new republic for help.

we see the new republic HQ as they‚Äôre hanging out and playing pool, we meetup with carson teva, new republic pilot from season 2 who offered cara dune a job. He plays the hologram from greef carga who‚Äôs asking for his help. Zebb walks up to him, and this is his live action debut. Zebb was in Rebels and he was part of the crew with ezra, hera, kanan, and chopper. It‚Äôs great seeing him in live action, and i think his appearance is perhaps a foreshadowing of ezra and thrawn. In fact, maybe he‚Äôs just stationed there to get intel on moff gideon‚Äôs transport time and date, so that sabine could escort him out and get information on where Thrawn is, leading them to Ezra. This theory comes from one of you during the watch party last night, and your reasoning for this was because beskar was found on the ship, this beskar could be sabine‚Äôs. Personally, I think it was mandalorians related to death watch, loyal to maul.

Carson Teva shows the hologram of Greef Carga to corsucant‚Äôs new republic HQ, colonel tuttle which is like the main center for it. He denies him approval to help, as G86 walks in after seeing Carson in there. She is still playing the new republic, and i think she still works for moff gideon. Carson mentions moff gideon having never made it to trial, and G86 is seen looking down in discomfort. She says a pretty imperial thing, by saying Navarro 7 may now see the importance of joining the new republic by essentially suffering. New republic denies help to nevarro 7, and carson takes it upon himself to go find the mandalorian. He tracks them down via R5‚Äôs transponder. He tells them about Greef Carga‚Äôs message, and then leaves.
Din speaks to the clan, holding the armorer‚Äôs hammer, which is like a talking stick type of thing. Mando pleads his case to save Greef Carga, who he says has had a change of heart against mandalorians, and that imperials were the ones who decimated the mandalorians, not Carga. He proposes they all live on navarro 7 as Greef has offered him land, and may offer them land too.

Carson Teva comes across an abandoned Lamda T4A shuttle. It looks heavily attacked. He speaks with the New Republic, and they find out its the ship that transported moff gideon. The ship has no survivors yet moff gideon‚Äôs body is missing. The flight crew are frozen from space. Carson Teva notices something embedded in the wall, it‚Äôs a piece of beskar, and they deduce that moff gideon was broken out of there by mandalorians. So, this could be one of two things. Either death watch, a very rugged and violent group of mandalorians did indeed break moff gideon out, which is believable since he did hold the dark saber at one point, meaning he accrued a following of some kind, a following that may still be very loyal to him. Or the other option is that he framed mandalorians by putting a piece of beskar there to throw the new republic off their tracks. The third option here is that he‚Äôs just paying mandalorians with beskar, as we know he has tons. I personally think he actually was freed from mandalorians who were perhaps loyal to darth maul once, and now loyal to moff gideon. I think once Bo Katan goes to unite these kinds of mandalorians, she will come to a very rude awakening and perhaps be captured herself, luring Din Djarin out to Moff Gideon, who will challenge him to a duel and this time win, claiming the dark saber for himself once again, and him being the one to rule all of the mandalorians.

title: TROLLS BAND TOGETHER | Official Trailer
description:
Trolls Band Together - In Theaters this Fall

This holiday season, get ready for an action-packed, all-star, rainbow-colored family reunion like no other as Anna Kendrick and Justin Timberlake return for the new chapter in DreamWorks Animation‚Äôs blockbuster musical franchise: Trolls Band Together. 

After two films of true friendship and relentless flirting, Poppy (Anna Kendrick) and Branch (Justin Timberlake) are now officially, finally, a couple (#broppy)! As they grow closer, Poppy discovers that Branch has a secret past. He was once part of her favorite boyband phenomenon, BroZone, with his four brothers: Floyd (Golden Globe nominated electropop sensation Troye Sivan), John Dory (Eric Andr√©; Sing 2), Spruce (Grammy winner Daveed Diggs; Hamilton) and Clay (Grammy winner Kid Cudi; Don‚Äôt Look Up). BroZone disbanded when Branch was still a baby, as did the family, and Branch hasn‚Äôt seen his brothers since.  

But when Branch‚Äôs bro Floyd is kidnapped for his musical talents by a pair of nefarious pop-star villains‚ÄîVelvet (Emmy winner Amy Schumer; Trainwreck) and Veneer (Grammy winner and Tony nominee Andrew Rannells; The Book of Mormon)‚ÄîBranch and Poppy embark on a harrowing and emotional journey to reunite the other brothers and rescue Floyd from a fate even worse than pop-culture obscurity. 

Featuring Trolls‚Äô signature psychedelic joy-bomb of new and classic pop hits, Trolls Band Together stars a dazzling cast of musical superstars and comedic powerhouses as new franchise characters, including four-time Grammy nominee and Latin Grammy winner Camila Cabello (Cinderella) as Viva; Zosia Mamet (The Flight Attendant) as Crimp; and 12-time Emmy winning drag icon RuPaul Charles as Miss Maxine. 

The returning cast includes Grammy, Emmy and Golden Globe nominee Zooey Deschanel as Bridget; Christopher Mintz-Plasse as Gristle, the Icona Pop duo Aino Jawo and Caroline Hjelt as Satin and Chenille, Grammy winner Anderson .Paak as Prince D, comedian Ron Funches as Cooper, SAG nominee Kunal Nayyar as Guy Diamond and Emmy winning Saturday Night Live legend Kenan Thompson as Tiny Diamond. 

Trolls Band Together is steered by returning director Walt Dohrn and producer Gina Shay, and is co-directed by Tim Heitz (head of story, Trolls World Tour). DreamWorks Animation‚Äôs Trolls films‚Äî2016‚Äôs Trolls and 2020‚Äôs Trolls World Tour‚Äîhave sung and danced their way to record-breaking success, earning an Oscar¬Æ nomination for Best Original Song and fueling one of the largest and most beloved entertainment brands in the world.

description:
Watch the Mark Twain Prize for American Humor celebrating Adam Sandler on CNN.com or CNNgo.

https://www.kennedy-center.org/whats-on/marktwain/

The Kennedy Center's Mark Twain Prize, which is named to honor one of the world‚Äôs greatest humorists, was awarded to Adam Sandler at a gala performance featuring some of the biggest names in comedy -- including Chris Rock, Conan O'Brien, Ben Stiller, Dana Carvey, Pete Davidson, Drew Barrymore, Jennifer Anniston, Idina Menzel, David Spade, and more -- on March 19, 2023, and aired nationally on CNN on March 26, 2023.

The Mark Twain Prize for American Humor recognizes individuals who have had an impact on American society in ways similar to the distinguished 19th-century novelist and essayist Samuel Clemens, best known as Mark Twain. As a social commentator, satirist, and creator of characters, Clemens was a fearless observer of society, who startled many while delighting and informing many more with his uncompromising perspective on social injustice and personal folly.

‚ÄúAdam Sandler has entertained audiences for over three decades with his films, music, and his tenure as a fan favorite cast member on SNL,‚Äù said Kennedy Center President Deborah F. Rutter about this year‚Äôs recipient. ‚ÄúAdam has created characters that have made us laugh, cry, and cry from laughing. I am looking forward to a laughter-filled evening like no other as we celebrate his career at a ceremony that is sure to bring together the best in comedy.‚Äù

title: Elemental | Official Trailer
description:
This Summer, meet the residents of Element City

Watch the new trailer for Disney and Pixar‚Äôs #Elemental and see the movie in 3D, only in theaters June 16!

Check out a brand-new trailer for Disney and Pixar‚Äôs ‚ÄúElemental,‚Äù an all-new original feature film that transports moviegoers to an extraordinary place called Element City, where a host of elements live and work. The trailer showcases each element‚Äîair, earth, water and fire‚Äîand what sets them apart according to Ember, a quick-witted and fiery woman who‚Äôs always stayed close to home in Firetown. In ‚ÄúElemental,‚Äù which opens in theaters on June 16, she finally ventures out of her comfort zone to explore this spectacular world born from the imaginations of Pixar‚Äôs filmmakers and specifically crafted for the big-screen experience. Element City is inspired by big cities around the globe and embraces theorized contributions from each elemental community‚Äîfrom giant pine-tree-like buildings and waterfall skyscrapers to a tornado-shaped arena called Cyclone Stadium. 

Joining the previously announced voice cast including Leah Lewis and Mamoudou Athie as Ember and Wade, respectively, are Ronnie del Carmen as Ember‚Äôs soon-to-be retired dad, Bernie; Shila Ommi as Ember‚Äôs love-seeking mom, Cinder; Wendi McLendon-Covey as Wade‚Äôs stormy and Air-Ball-loving boss, Gale; Catherine O‚ÄôHara as Wade‚Äôs welcoming mom, Brook; Mason Wertheimer as Ember‚Äôs admiring earth neighbor, Clod; and Joe Pera as an overgrown city bureaucrat, Fern.
 
Directed by Peter Sohn, produced by Denise Ream, p.g.a., and executive produced by Pete Docter, ‚ÄúElemental‚Äù features a screenplay by John Hoberg & Kat Likkel and Brenda Hsueh with story by Sohn, Hoberg & Likkel and Hsueh. The film‚Äôs original score was composed and conducted by Thomas Newman.
